cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with safety challenges in automated driving, which is a robotics application. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of probabilistic and machine learning methods for minimizing risk. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is mentioned in the paper as the field-of-view of the ego vehicle is used to identify critical sensing field edges. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is mentioned in the paper as the proposed method can verify the safety of given trajectories w.r.t. arbitrary safe-state formulations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also mentioned in the paper as the paper discusses the limitations of probabilistic and machine learning methods in guaranteeing safety.
